The paper focuses on visual understanding and reasoning, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of natural language processing and multiple choice questions suggests a connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL). The development of a new dataset and approach for generating non-trivial problems could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO).
